modules.description: Provides functions to count occurrences of elements in a list, calculate the frequency of each unique element, and return the total number of elements. Works with lists of any type, including integers, strings, and custom types. Used to analyze data distributions in log processing and statistical sampling.

Returns the number of hardware cores available on the current machine as a native integer. Operates directly on system-level thread concurrency information. Used to optimize parallel task distribution in performance-critical applications.
